12:["$","div",null,{"className":"prose prose-invert prose-lg max-w-none mb-16 [&_h2]:font-extrabold [&_h2]:tracking-tight [&_h2]:text-foreground [&_h2]:mt-12 [&_h2]:mb-4 [&_h3]:font-bold [&_h3]:text-foreground [&_h3]:mt-8 [&_h3]:mb-3 [&_p]:text-muted-foreground [&_p]:leading-relaxed [&_li]:text-muted-foreground [&_strong]:text-foreground","children":[["$","h2","h2-0",{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"The Short Answer"}],"\n",["$","p","p-0",{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed mb-4","children":"Most crypto yield doesn't meet institutional standards. Staking is directionally exposed. DeFi farming carries smart contract and governance risk. Lending yields compress to near-zero in bear markets. The strategies that survive institutional due diligence share common traits: market neutrality, diversified counterparty exposure, transparent reporting, and yield from structural market features rather than token incentives."}],"\n",["$","p","p-1",{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed mb-4","children":"Cross-exchange funding rate arbitrage checks these boxes. It's not the only institutional-grade strategy, but it's one of the few that generates yield regardless of market direction."}],"\n",["$","h2","h2-1",{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Why Most Crypto Yield Fails Institutional Due Diligence"}],"\n",["$","h3","h3-0",{"className":"text-lg font-bold text-foreground mt-8 mb-3","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Directional Exposure"}],"\n",["$","p","p-2",{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed mb-4","children":["Staking ETH at ",["$","a","a-0",{"href":"https://www.datawallet.com/crypto/ethereum-staking-statistics-and-trends","className":"text-primary underline underline-offset-2 hover:text-primary/80 transition-colors","target":"_blank","rel":"noopener noreferrer","children":"3.3% APY"}]," means you're holding ETH. If ETH drops 40%, your net return is deeply negative. Most institutional mandates can't justify a 40% drawdown for 3.3% yield. The risk-return profile doesn't pass basic portfolio construction tests."]}],"\n",["$","h3","h3-1",{"className":"text-lg font-bold text-foreground mt-8 mb-3","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Smart Contract Risk"}],"\n",["$","p","p-3",{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed mb-4","children":"DeFi protocols (Aave, Compound, Curve, Pendle) introduce smart contract risk — the possibility that a bug, exploit, or governance attack drains deposited funds. While top protocols are heavily audited, the risk is non-zero and difficult to quantify for institutional risk models."}],"\n",["$","h3","h3-2",{"className":"text-lg font-bold text-foreground mt-8 mb-3","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Yield Source Sustainability"}],"\n",["$","p","p-4",{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed mb-4","children":"Token incentive programs (liquidity mining, governance token rewards) are temporary. When incentives end, yield collapses. Institutions need yield sources that are structural, not promotional."}],"\n",["$","h3","h3-3",{"className":"text-lg font-bold text-foreground mt-8 mb-3","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Counterparty Concentration"}],"\n",["$","p","p-5",{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed mb-4","children":"Single-venue strategies (Ethena on 3-4 exchanges, HLP on Hyperliquid alone) concentrate risk. Institutions learned from FTX that exchange counterparty risk is real and under-priced."}],"\n","$L15","\n","$L16","\n","$L17","\n","$L18","\n","$L19","\n","$L1a","\n","$L1b","\n","$L1c","\n","$L1d","\n","$L1e","\n","$L1f","\n","$L20","\n","$L21","\n","$L22","\n","$L23","\n","$L24","\n","$L25","\n","$L26","\n","$L27","\n","$L28","\n","$L29","\n","$L2a","\n","$L2b","\n","$L2c","\n","$L2d","\n","$L2e","\n","$L2f","\n","$L30","\n","$L31","\n","$L32","\n","$L33","\n","$L34","\n","$L35","\n","$L36","\n","$L37","\n","$L38","\n","$L39","\n","$L3a"]}]
